properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued February 9 at 6:44AM CST until February 9 at 9:00PM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW EXPECTED ACROSS CENTRAL AND EAST-CENTRAL WISCONSIN
TODAY...

.A low pressure system located over extreme northwest Iowa at
daybreak will track to northeast Iowa by noon, then along the
Wisconsin/Illinois border this afternoon. This is a rather compact
but vigorous storm system, and will bring a significant snowfall
to all but far northern Wisconsin. The storm is also fast moving,
so snow will quickly overspread the area during the morning, but
also diminish quickly from west to east during the late afternoon
and evening.

Although winds are not expected to be strong during the storm,
the heavy snowfall could reduce the visibility to under 1/4 mile
at times, especially in central and east-central Wisconsin. This
will likely result in hazardous travel conditions. Air travel is
also likely to be affected by the storm.

* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 5 to
10 inches, with the lower totals occurring north of Green Bay.

* WHERE...Portions of east-central and northeast Wisconsin.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM CST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Travel will become difficult due to snow covered
roads and greatly reduced visibility in the heavy snow.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Snow will spread east across the area this
morning, reaching the northern portion of Door county by
lunchtime. The snow will quickly become heavy. The fast onset
of heavy snow is likely to result in very rapidly deteriorating
travel conditions during the middle to late morning.
properties.instruction:
If traveling during the storm, expect to drive at a much slower
than normal speed and allow plenty of time to reach your
destination. Be sure to take some food and water along with you
in your vehicle in case of an emergency. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM CST THIS EVENING
